Ball, 1966a: 26. Type locality: &quot;Aklavik, N[orth]w[est] T[erritories]&quot; (original citation). Holotype (â™‚) in CAS [# 9316]. Etymology. This species was named after the Canadian Joseph Dewey Soper [1893-1982], arctic explorer, zoologist, and prolific author. Soper, as biologist for the Canadian Wildlife Service, made important contributions to the knowledge of arctic birds and mammals and to arctic geography.
</paragraph>
